                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4 A 2/273: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Persia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-02-12T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1925—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Your No. 9, February 9, 4 p.m. Referring to Department’s No. 4, February 7, 3
                    p.m., you may substitute “with respect to” for “toward suppressing illicit” in
                    note to Persian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
